Maxwell Field Formalism [Definition] : Maxwell Field is the field of 4-vector. The Lagrangian is Lorentz Scalar constructed by the so-called Electromagnetic Tensor: $$\mathcal{L}=- rac 1 4 F^{\mu
u}F_{\mu
u}$$ And where $F_{\mu
u}=\partial_{\mu}A_{
u}-\partial_{
u}A_{\mu}$ is an anti-symmetry tensor. This form will let the zero components of conjugate field vanish because it is independent of $\partial_0 A_0$ .
